RunInfo:
  Drell-Yan Z -> ee / mu mu + jets at sqrt(s) = 13 TeV. Generate inclusive or
  HT/pT-sliced DY samples; both Z decay channels (ee, mumu) are combined.
NeedCrossSection: yes
Beams: [p+, p+]
Energies: [13000]
Description:
  'Particle-level (fiducial) measurement of the mass of the AK8 jet recoiling
  against a Z boson in Z(ll)+jet events, both ungroomed and after soft-drop
  grooming (beta = 0, z_cut = 0.1). The fiducial region is defined by exactly
  two same-flavour opposite-sign dressed leptons (electrons pT > 40 GeV, muons
  pT > 29 GeV, |eta| < 2.4), with pT(Z) > 90 GeV and 71 < m(ll) < 111 GeV. The
  candidate jet is the highest-pT anti-kT R = 0.8 jet with |y| < 2.4, separated
  from both leptons by dR > 0.4, back-to-back with the Z (dphi > 1.57) and
  balanced in pT (|pTZ - pTjet|/(pTZ + pTjet) < 0.3). Jet mass and
  rho = 2*log10(m/(pT*R)) are measured in jet-pT bins [200, 290, 400, inf] GeV.
  This routine reproduces the generator-level selection of the coffea
  QJetMassProcessor used in the analysis.'
